        "name": "Discretization error GCI acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI) study performed on three systematically refined meshes (4.2 M, 8.7 M, 17.4 M cells) using Richardson extrapolation. GCI for hemolysis index QoI must be below 5% on the medium mesh used for production runs."
      },
      "rationale": "A three-mesh GCI study was conducted per Celik et al. (2008). The computed GCI on the 8.7 M production mesh was 3.1% for hemolysis index and 2.8% for area-averaged wall shear stress, both below the 5% acceptance threshold. Observed order of convergence p = 1.94, consistent with second-order spatial discretization. Discretization error is well-characterized and bounded."
    },
    {
