        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions fidelity acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, hematocrit) must be reproduced in the CFD model within ±2% of the reported experimental values for all five operating points."
      },
      "rationale": "All five PIV and hemolysis bench test conditions (flow rates 2.5–6.0 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM) were replicated in the CFD model using measured inlet velocity profiles and rotational MRF zones. Fluid properties (viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s, density 1056 kg/m³, hematocrit 35%) match reported experimental values within 1.5%. Temperature was held constant at 37°C in both bench and simulation."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/output-comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
